'''''Lunar Bird''''' is an abstract bronze sculpture by [[Joan Miró]]. It was modeled in 1945, enlarged in 1966, and cast in 1967.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!373166~!0#focus' |title=Lunar Bird, (sculpture) |website=Siris-artinventories.si.edu |date= |accessdate=2017-04-18}}</ref>

It is in the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hirshhorn.si.edu/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=10294 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081023135704/http://hirshhorn.si.edu/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=10294 |archivedate=2008-10-23 |df= }}</ref>

