{{for|the online, editable copy of this work|Help:Wikipedia: The Missing Manual}} {{correct title|reason=namespace|Wikipedia: The Missing Manual}} {{Infobox book | name = Wikipedia: The Missing Manual | image = Wikipedia - The Missing Manual 9780596515164 lrg.jpg | caption = | author = John Broughton | country = United States | language = English | series = The Missing Manuals | subject = [[Wikipedia]] | genre = [[how-to]] | publisher = [[O'Reilly Media]] | pub_date = 2008 | media_type = paperback | isbn = 0-596-51516-2 | congress = TK5105.8882.W54 B76 2008 | oclc = 191883897 }} '''''Wikipedia: The Missing Manual''''' is a 2008 book by John Broughton. It is a [[how-to]] guide that explains the process of contributing to the Internet encyclopedia [[Wikipedia]].<ref name="charms">{{cite web|url=http://www.nybooks.com/articles/21131 |title=The Charms of Wikipedia |last=Baker |first=Nicholson |authorlink=Nicholson Baker |publisher=[[The New York Review of Books]] |volume=55 |issue=4 |date=March 20, 2008}}</ref>
"For anyone who is interested in becoming part of the noble experiment, this book is an excellent introduction," wrote reviewer [[Robert Slade]].<ref name="Slade">"Wikipedia: The Missing Manual", BKWKPDMM.RVW, a review by [[Robert Slade]], The Internet Review Project, 2008</ref> ''Wikipedia: The Missing Manual'' is part of [[O'Reilly Media]]'s Missing Manual series,<ref>[https://www.oreilly.com/missingmanuals/ O'Reilly Missing Manual series]</ref> which was created by [[David Pogue]], technology columnist for ''[[The New York Times]]'' and ''[[Scientific American]]''.
On January 26, 2009, O'Reilly announced that the content of the book was being released under a [[free license]] [[License compatibility|compatible]] with Wikipedia and that it would be available for editing in the Help area of Wikipedia.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://press.oreilly.com/pub/pr/2216 |title=Wikipedia: The Missing Manual Posted on Wikipedia--O'Reilly Media Alert: Edit the Book on Wikipedia |publisher=[[O'Reilly Media]] |date=January 26, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715103527/http://openeducationnews.org/2009/01/28/wikipedia-the-missing-manual-posted-on-wikipedia/|archivedate=July 15, 2014 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>
The book has a spin-off, '''''Wikipedia Reader's Guide: The Missing Manual''''', consisting of Appendix B (slightly expanded) and Chapter 1 from the book.
==See also== {{Wikipedia books|Wikipedia: The Missing Manual|position=left}} * [[Help:Wikipedia: The Missing Manual|Help:''Wikipedia: The Missing Manual'']] (an online editable copy) * ''[[How Wikipedia Works]]'' * [[Bibliography of Wikipedia]] * [[:File:Wikipedia Training Manual.pdf|State Library of Queensland's Exploring Wikipedia Content Creation Training Manual]] at Wikimedia Commons
